cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use SubstrATE in your research, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "SubstrATE: Substrate Annotation Tool for Enzymes"
abstract: "A command-line pipeline for identifying and annotating
  polysaccharide utilisation loci (PULs) and CAZyme gene clusters
  (CGCs) in bacterial genomes. Supports 25 built-in substrates,
  automated phylogenetic tree building, synteny visualisation,
  and activity annotation."
version: 0.1.0
date-released: 2025-04-24
license: MIT
repository-code: https://github.com/MahumFarhan/substrATE
authors:
  - family-names: "Farhan"
    given-names: "Mahum"
    orcid: "0000-0002-2771-5300"
    affiliation: "University of Bremen"
keywords:
  - CAZymes
  - polysaccharide utilisation loci
  - PUL
  - glycoside hydrolases
  - marine bacteria
  - bioinformatics
  - phylogenetics
references:
